  "enforcementPrinciples": [
    "Backend authorization is authoritative.",
    "Frontend route guards are supplementary.",
    "Authentication does not imply authorization.",
    "JWT-only routes are AUTH_ONLY, not permission guarded.",
    "Every protected route must declare an authentication policy.",
    "Every business action must declare a permission.",
    "Every route must declare tenant and site scope behavior.",
    "Package entitlement and enablement are independent from permissions.",
    "Sensitive reads, mutations, controls and exports require audit policy.",
    "Commands and intake operations require declared idempotency behavior.",
    "Service identities receive explicit machine permissions only.",
    "Role names must not be hardcoded into business services.",
    "Public routes must be explicitly allowlisted.",
    "Legacy compatibility does not exempt a route from classification.",
    "Enforcement rollout must support compatibility stages without silently weakening policy."
  ],
